' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' INFRASTRUCTURE DATA CLASSES (from JSON/env — not markdown)
' ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
package "Infrastructure Data Classes (from storage.json, run_config.json, .env)" #E6E6E6 {

  note as InfraNote
    Passive @dataclasses from JSON/env.
    Describes where/how to run, not what data exists.
    Used by: All three paths
  end note

  class RootsConfig <<dataclass>> {
    + raw : str
    + bronze : str
    + silver : str
  }

  note bottom of RootsConfig
    Different physical storage:
    raw = HDD/NAS (bulk, archival)
    bronze + silver = SSD (fast scans)
  end note

  class ApiLimits <<dataclass>> {
    + duckdb_memory_limit : str
